                </row>
            </thead>
             <tbody>
                 <row>
                     <entry morerows="1"></entry>
                     <entry></entry>
                 </row>
                <row>
                    <entry><emphasis role="args">int16 random value</emphasis></entry>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
    <abstract>
        <para>Push the a random int16 value onto the stack. The number will be between -32767 and 32767.</para>
        <para>
            Note that this instruction is inherited from the Cricket Logo virtual machine. To provide control
            over the range of random numbers returned, there is also
            <olink targetptr="asm_randomxy">randomxy</olink>.</para>
     </abstract>
    <sect2>
        <title>Synopsis</title>
        <funcsynopsis>
            <para><command>random</command></para>
        </funcsynopsis>
    </sect2>
    <sect2>
        <title>Arguments</title>
            <para>Nil.</para>

    </sect2>
    <sect2>
        <title>Returns</title>
        <para>
            Returns a random number between -32767 and 32767 (ie. int16).
        </para>
    </sect2>
